'''Barış Alper Yılmaz''' (born 23 May 2000) is a Turkish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Yılmaz started football in 2011 in Rize İl Özel İdarespor. In 2017, he was transferred to [[Ankara Demirspor]], one of the third league teams. After playing here for three seasons, he was transferred to [[Ankara Keçiörengücü]], which was promoted to the first league.

===Galatasaray===
Yılmaz transferred to [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] on 9 July 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/hos-geldin-baris-alper-yilmaz/48959|title=Hoş geldin Barış Alper Yılmaz|website=www.galatasaray.org|access-date=25 July 2021|archive-date=9 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709140125/https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/hos-geldin-baris-alper-yilmaz/48959|url-status=live}}</ref> His contract was extended by Galatasaray on 4 May 2023 to be valid until the end of the 2026–27 season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/baris-alper-yilmazin-sozlesmesi-uzatildi/53189 |title=Barış Alper Yılmaz'ın sözleşmesi uzatıldı |publisher=www.galatasaray.org |date=4 May 2023 |access-date=5 May 2023 |archive-date=5 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230505084758/https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/baris-alper-yilmazin-sozlesmesi-uzatildi/53189 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Yılmaz became the champion in the [[Süper Lig]] in the [[2022–23 Süper Lig|2022–23]] season with the Galatasaray team. Defeating [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]] 4–1 away in the match played in the 36th week on 30 May 2023, Galatasaray secured the lead with two weeks before the end and won the 23rd championship in its history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65761517|title=Turkish Super Lig: Galatasaray win title for 23rd time after beating Ankaragucu 4-1|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 May 2023|access-date=31 May 2023|archive-date=2 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230602093025/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65761517|url-status=live}}</ref>

Yılmaz scored his first UEFA Champions League goal for Galatasaray on 25 February 2026 against Juventus, in a game Galatasaray lost 3-2 but advanced 7-5 on aggregate. On 26 April 2026 he scored his first goal against Fenerbahçe in a 3-0 win from a penalty kick.

==International career==
Yılmaz played three matches with the Turkey under-21 national football team and scored 1 goal. He debuted with the senior [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] in a 6–0 win over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] on 13 November 2021.<ref name="Global Sports Archive 2021">{{cite web | title=Match Report of Turkey vs Gibraltar - 2021-11-13 - WC Qualification | website=Global Sports Archive | date=13 November 2021 | url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-11-13/turkey-vs-gibraltar/2236805/ | access-date=13 November 2021 | archive-date=13 November 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211113235550/https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-11-13/turkey-vs-gibraltar/2236805/ | url-status=live }}</ref>

On 12 October 2023, Yılmaz scored his first goal for Türkiye in a 1–0 [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] win over [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.optus.com.au/news/uefa-euro-2024-qualifiers/os64468/uefa-euro-2024-qualifiers-talking-points-erling-haaland-norway-27-goals-cyprus|title=UEFA Euro 2024 qualifiers Talking Points: Erling Haaland makes it 27 goals in 27 appearances for Norway|date=13 October 2023|publisher=Optus|access-date=13 October 2023|archive-date=8 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231108103933/https://sport.optus.com.au/news/uefa-euro-2024-qualifiers/os64468/uefa-euro-2024-qualifiers-talking-points-erling-haaland-norway-27-goals-cyprus|url-status=live}}</ref>

He was named in Turkey's 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=7 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240607205837/https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |url-status=live }}</ref>

